#CHIP YMF262
#CLOCK 14318180

; OPL3 (YMF262) 4-operator FM Test
;
; The YMF262 OPL3 is an enhanced version of OPL2 that doubles the channels
; and supports 4-operator FM synthesis (pairing two 2-op channels).
;
; OPL3 has 18 channels total (9 pairs), each pair can be:
; - Two independent 2-op channels (OPL2 mode)
; - One 4-op channel (OPL3 mode)
;
; Tests:
; - 4-operator FM synthesis
; - Complex timbral possibilities
; - Register accuracy for 4-op patches

#TRACK 0

TEMPO 120

; 4-operator channels (pairs 1-3): Complex lead synth
c4 . d4 . e4 .

r4

; 4-operator channels (pairs 4-6): Rich pad
f4 . . g4 . .

r4

; 2-operator channels (remaining): Bass and drums
c3 . d3 . e3 .

r4

r2

#END
